Avoids:
error: call to undeclared function 'setusershell'
Android does not have /etc/shells, so 
Termux chsh only checks if the shell is in /data/data/com.termux/files/usr/bin if relative,
and if absolute, it only checks if it is executable and not
/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/bin/login.
This patch simply stubs is_known_shell() by always returning true.
print_shells() has no meaningful purpose that can be guessed at on Android, so this stubs it to no-op.
print_shells() is not used in anything except util-linux chsh, which is not built in Termux.

--- a/lib/shells.c
+++ b/lib/shells.c
@@ -65,7 +65,7 @@ extern void print_shells(FILE *out, const char *format)
 	}
 	econf_free(keys);
 	econf_free(key_file);
-#else
+#elif !defined(__ANDROID__)
 	char *s;
 
 	setusershell();
@@ -107,6 +107,8 @@ extern int is_known_shell(const char *shell_name)
 
 	free(val);
 	econf_free(key_file);
+#elif defined(__ANDROID__)
+	return 1;
 #else
 	char *s;
 
